                <note type="summary">
                    
                        <p>This letter is Andrew Phillip Magill (1871-1941), private secretary to the chief secretary of Ireland (Augustine Birrell in 1916) responding to the M.P. of North Leitrim Francis E. Meehan (d. 1946). The letter informs Meehan that he had received Meehan&#39;s previous letter suggesting Mr Thomas W. Delany for the position of Chief Crown Solicitor which had been vacated on the death of Sir Malachy J. Kelly.</p>
                    
